WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:09.574
- Previously, on "Shooter..."
- Don't be the man that ruins

00:10.662 --> 00:11.315
not only his life,
but the lives

00:11.359 --> 00:12.621
of those around him.

00:12.664 --> 00:14.144
What do you think
I'd be willing to do

00:14.188 --> 00:16.146
to your family?
- Do anything to them

00:16.190 --> 00:18.366
your body will hit the ground
before you even hear a gunshot.

00:18.409 --> 00:21.412
- You know I'm willing
to take that chance.

00:21.456 --> 00:23.197
Are you?
- Does Bob Lee know how

00:23.240 --> 00:24.807
to stop these people?

00:24.850 --> 00:26.504
- Bob Lee's on the other side
of the country.

00:26.548 --> 00:28.071
We have to take care
of ourselves.

00:28.115 --> 00:30.378
I have to relocate us, now.

00:30.421 --> 00:32.336
- Drop your weapons!
Everyone step away

00:32.380 --> 00:34.469
from Judge Brooks
or we will open fire!

00:34.512 --> 00:36.384
- You're going to prison,
not the Supreme Court.

00:36.427 --> 00:38.560
- Swagger!
This is how a patriot dies.

00:38.603 --> 00:40.562
[dramatic music]

00:40.605 --> 00:41.824
[phone ringing]

00:41.867 --> 00:43.478
- Brooks is dead.

00:43.521 --> 00:46.524
There are no protocols
if there is no Atlas.

00:46.568 --> 00:49.440
You and I are not finished.
- I never said I was.

00:49.484 --> 00:55.316
♪

00:55.359 --> 00:57.579
- Bob Lee Swagger?
We need to take you in.

00:57.622 --> 00:59.624
- What?

00:59.668 --> 01:01.104
I need to get to my family,
Nadine.

01:01.148 --> 01:02.714
Tell 'em I'm coming.

01:11.158 --> 01:13.116
- Don't say anything
but "lawyer."

01:15.684 --> 01:17.773
[door buzzes]

01:19.253 --> 01:21.255
- Have a seat, gentlemen.

01:21.298 --> 01:28.131
♪

01:28.175 --> 01:30.742
What were you doing
in those woods?

01:30.786 --> 01:32.614
- Lawyer.

01:34.268 --> 01:35.878
- I'm sorry,
are we under arrest?

01:35.921 --> 01:38.141
- Not yet.

01:38.185 --> 01:39.664
- So, then, we don't have
to answer your questions.

01:39.708 --> 01:41.188
- Then I'll detain you

01:41.231 --> 01:43.538
for obstructing
a federal investigation.

01:43.581 --> 01:47.194
♪

01:47.237 --> 01:49.848
- Is that a--
a drainage ditch, right?

01:49.892 --> 01:51.459
What is that?
- It's a grave.

01:52.808 --> 01:54.679
So you used to work
for Senator Hayes.

01:54.723 --> 01:55.898
- Uh, I did.

01:59.206 --> 02:00.816
- I got
a Supreme Court Justice nominee

02:00.859 --> 02:02.687
with a hole in his head

02:02.731 --> 02:04.733
and five dead mercenaries.

02:04.776 --> 02:07.170
And I got you two pricks
sitting here acting like

02:07.214 --> 02:08.954
it's just another day.

02:08.998 --> 02:10.869
- We were out for a walk--
- Shut up.

02:13.176 --> 02:14.830
Swagger.

02:15.744 --> 02:17.267
You know what it's like

02:17.311 --> 02:20.792
to have the entire
U.S. government on your ass.

02:20.836 --> 02:23.621
So tell me, what were you doing
in those woods

02:23.665 --> 02:25.362
with Justice Brooks?

02:27.277 --> 02:28.452
- Lawyer.

02:29.845 --> 02:33.283
- Brooks begged us to take him
into those woods.

02:33.327 --> 02:34.937
He feared for his life.

02:34.980 --> 02:36.808
He trusted no one, least of all
his own security detail.

02:36.852 --> 02:38.462
He knew there were people
out to get him

02:38.506 --> 02:40.203
for what he did in Vietnam,
and he was right.

02:40.247 --> 02:42.292
- Doesn't explain the grave.
- Those, uh, mercenaries,

02:42.336 --> 02:44.860
as you called them,
they dug that.

02:44.903 --> 02:46.514
Soon as Brooks saw it,
he knew there was no way

02:46.557 --> 02:48.211
he was making it out
of those woods alive,

02:48.255 --> 02:51.823
so he chose to go out
on his own terms.

02:51.867 --> 02:53.999
Brave man. Honorable.

02:54.043 --> 02:58.830
♪

02:58.874 --> 03:00.223
So are we free to go?

03:00.267 --> 03:03.487
♪

03:03.531 --> 03:05.185
- Is he in?

03:08.753 --> 03:10.407
Thank you.

03:14.281 --> 03:15.369
[door closes]

03:29.644 --> 03:31.776
- What can I do for you, Red?

03:33.474 --> 03:36.651
- You asked for a draw-down
in Afghanistan,

03:36.694 --> 03:40.350
one where you could save face,

03:40.394 --> 03:41.569
and we handled it.

03:41.612 --> 03:43.353
Saved the country billions.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.312
Not to mention the human cost.

03:47.052 --> 03:49.533
- You told me you guys work
in the shadows.

03:49.577 --> 03:52.710
You want the Medal of Freedom?
- No, sir.

03:52.754 --> 03:54.495
But with Brooks' death,

03:54.538 --> 03:56.932
we are left in a tough spot.

03:56.975 --> 04:00.892
- Well, you asked me
to nominate him, and I did.

04:00.936 --> 04:03.068
Frankly, his suicide saved him
the embarrassment

04:03.112 --> 04:04.983
of not being confirmed.

04:05.027 --> 04:06.594
I can think
of at least three Senators

04:06.637 --> 04:08.291
who would have opposed him.

04:08.335 --> 04:09.727
- He would have been sitting
in the middle

04:09.771 --> 04:12.469
of that bench, sir, trust me.

04:12.513 --> 04:15.298
When you were doing sit-ups
on Parris Island.

04:15.342 --> 04:17.387
I was here, sir.

04:17.431 --> 04:21.043
Learning the ebb and flow
of life and death in D.C.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.698
- Life and death.
- The tree of liberty

04:23.741 --> 04:25.656
must be refreshed
from time to time

04:25.700 --> 04:27.310
with the blood of patriots.

04:27.354 --> 04:30.052
- You don't get
to quote Jefferson to me,

04:30.095 --> 04:33.403
and you sure as shit don't get
to come into this office,

04:33.447 --> 04:35.318
a place of dignity
and Democracy,

04:35.362 --> 04:38.278
and blithely condescend to me
about your plans for murder.

04:40.497 --> 04:42.369
I'm picking the next
Supreme Court nominee.

04:42.412 --> 04:45.633
Me. Not you
and your god damn cabal.

04:48.375 --> 04:51.856
- That is your prerogative,
sir...

04:51.900 --> 04:53.597
but be advised:

04:53.641 --> 04:56.339
For decades,
Presidents have stood

04:56.383 --> 04:58.776
on this seal, and told me...

04:58.820 --> 05:00.778
the very same thing.

05:00.822 --> 05:03.346
Usually early
in their first term,

05:03.390 --> 05:05.479
when they still thought
they had the power

05:05.522 --> 05:07.132
to get things done.

05:07.176 --> 05:09.004
But...

05:09.047 --> 05:11.789
somewhere toward the end
of that first term,

05:11.833 --> 05:14.357
when you realize
just how impotent

05:14.401 --> 05:16.881
you really are,
and how the things

05:16.925 --> 05:20.537
that we do quietly,
anonymously,

05:20.581 --> 05:22.539
change this nation
for the good.

05:22.583 --> 05:25.499
And when you want
that elusive second term,

05:25.542 --> 05:28.502
that's when you will invite me
back in here and thank me.

05:28.545 --> 05:29.807
But don't worry--
by that time,

05:29.851 --> 05:32.114
I will have forgotten
this conversation.

05:32.157 --> 05:34.464
- [chuckles]

05:34.508 --> 05:36.074
You don't run this country.

05:36.118 --> 05:37.641
I do.

05:37.685 --> 05:39.948
At the will of the greatest
source of power:

05:39.991 --> 05:41.602
the American people.

05:42.994 --> 05:44.735
- They're fickle.

05:44.779 --> 05:46.128
We're loyal.

05:46.171 --> 05:47.999
That's the reason
that you and I are on

05:48.043 --> 05:50.088
the same evacuation plan, sir.

05:50.132 --> 05:52.482
You need me
much more than them.

05:52.526 --> 05:55.006
But forget who
your friends are,

05:55.050 --> 05:57.052
and all those things
that we do for you,

05:57.095 --> 05:58.836
and the darkness
will suddenly see

05:58.880 --> 06:00.577
the light of day.

06:01.926 --> 06:03.798
You won't survive it.

06:06.148 --> 06:07.497
- Get out.

06:08.803 --> 06:11.196
- Mr. President.

06:11.240 --> 06:16.637
♪

06:16.680 --> 06:19.640
[dramatic music]

06:19.683 --> 06:26.734
♪

06:35.699 --> 06:36.091
.

06:36.134 --> 06:37.875
[knocking]

06:43.272 --> 06:45.492
both: Hey.
- Did you sleep okay?

06:45.535 --> 06:48.190
- Yeah, if you wanna
call it that.

06:48.233 --> 06:50.453
- Look, I need you to take Mary
to Edie Poole's, okay?

06:50.497 --> 06:52.890
You guys are gonna
be safe there.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.588
- Where are you going?

06:54.631 --> 06:56.633
- I'm gonna go see Bob Lee.

06:56.677 --> 06:59.419
I can't keep living like this.

06:59.462 --> 07:01.464
[somber music]

07:01.508 --> 07:03.031
Here--

07:03.074 --> 07:04.467
Here's the address, okay?
- Okay.

07:04.511 --> 07:06.034
- She knows you're coming.

07:06.077 --> 07:07.339
No one will think to look
for you guys there.

07:07.383 --> 07:08.950
No credit cards.

07:08.993 --> 07:10.125
Don't take the same route home,
do a lap around--

07:10.168 --> 07:11.996
- I know.
I know.

07:13.302 --> 07:14.912
- Okay.
- Okay.

07:15.696 --> 07:17.524
Come here.

07:17.567 --> 07:20.396
You be strong...
- Yeah.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.615
- And you tell him
how you feel.

07:21.658 --> 07:22.964
He'll hear you.

07:25.357 --> 07:27.142
- Promise me you're
gonna be safe, okay?

07:27.185 --> 07:30.406
- I'm gonna take great care
of your girl, I promise you.

07:30.450 --> 07:32.364
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

07:32.408 --> 07:36.368
♪

07:36.412 --> 07:39.241
- Anything from Julie?
- Nothing.

07:39.284 --> 07:42.026
- Where's Isaac?
- He's gone dark.

07:42.070 --> 07:43.375
- I figured with Brooks dead,
this thing would be over,

07:43.419 --> 07:44.725
but it's not, is it?

07:44.768 --> 07:47.336
- Yeah, I don't see
any confetti or streamers.

07:47.379 --> 07:48.555
[phone vibrating]

07:48.598 --> 07:50.034
- Hold up.

07:51.035 --> 07:52.602
Hello?
- It's me.

07:52.646 --> 07:54.561
- Jules.
I've been trying to call you.

07:54.604 --> 07:56.171
Are you okay?
How's Mary?

07:56.214 --> 07:57.999
- Yeah, we're fine.
We're with Anne.

07:58.042 --> 08:00.697
We had to get off the grid.
- Good, you did good.

08:00.741 --> 08:03.570
- Coming to see you.
- You are? When?

08:03.613 --> 08:05.485
- Tonight.
Meet me at your hotel.

08:05.528 --> 08:07.443
- I can't wait.

08:07.487 --> 08:09.140
- I'll see you then.

08:11.752 --> 08:14.450
- That was Julie,
she's on her way here.

08:14.494 --> 08:18.106
- I'm glad she's okay.
- Yeah, well, no offense, uh--

08:18.149 --> 08:19.629
I need a break from you two.

08:19.673 --> 08:21.544
I'm gonna go see my buddy,
Van Tassell.

08:21.588 --> 08:23.546
You know, with Brooks gone,
maybe he knows

08:23.590 --> 08:25.113
who the next nominee is.

08:25.156 --> 08:27.463
See how far down
Atlas goes on this.

08:27.507 --> 08:29.465
- Well, don't use
your credit card.

08:29.509 --> 08:30.466
- And don't go home.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.686
- Yeah, no, I'm good.

08:32.729 --> 08:34.209
I'll be fine.
I'll get some more

08:34.252 --> 08:35.427
of that
pink pepper spray, right?

08:35.471 --> 08:36.646
- It's powerful shit.
- Yep.

08:36.690 --> 08:38.039
- Harris, wait.

08:43.087 --> 08:44.393
Take it.

08:46.482 --> 08:47.614
- Pretty sure I should have
a permit for that,

08:47.657 --> 08:49.703
but, uh, okay.

08:49.746 --> 08:52.140
- Hey, Buddy, you might wanna
slide that around

08:52.183 --> 08:54.055
closer to your hip,
unless you want a loaded gun

08:54.098 --> 08:55.578
pointing at your...
- Say no more.

08:55.622 --> 08:57.580
Thank you.

08:57.624 --> 08:58.712
All right.

09:00.104 --> 09:03.020
[suspenseful music]

09:03.064 --> 09:10.114
♪

09:20.168 --> 09:21.517
- Excuse me?

09:21.561 --> 09:23.345
Do either of you have a phone

09:23.388 --> 09:24.694
I could use right quick
to make a call?

09:24.738 --> 09:27.479
It's a local call.

09:27.523 --> 09:29.525
I can give you the number,
you can dial it.

09:29.569 --> 09:32.093
- Here, just use my phone.

09:32.136 --> 09:33.573
- Thank you.
- That's okay.

09:35.400 --> 09:38.316
[phone vibrating]

09:38.360 --> 09:44.845
♪

09:44.888 --> 09:47.369
- Hello?
- Nadine, it's me.

09:47.412 --> 09:49.197
I'm on Main and Frazier,
get here.

09:49.240 --> 09:50.677
- What's going on?
Where's your car?

09:50.720 --> 09:51.852
- Just get here.

09:51.895 --> 09:54.202
[line disconnects]

09:54.245 --> 10:01.252
♪

10:04.125 --> 10:05.605
- [grunts]

10:07.389 --> 10:08.608
- Are you okay?

10:10.392 --> 10:12.394
- [grunts]

10:12.437 --> 10:13.700
[breathing heavily]

10:13.743 --> 10:15.484
The guy who killed
Katherine Mayfield

10:15.527 --> 10:17.312
just tried to kill me.
- What?

10:17.355 --> 10:18.792
You sure it was the same guy?

10:18.835 --> 10:21.533
- Bob Lee and I
saw him take the shot.

10:21.577 --> 10:23.187
I trailed him to a warehouse,

10:23.231 --> 10:24.624
but he must have
seen me coming.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.408
He got my keys,
he got my phone,

10:26.451 --> 10:28.236
set the place on fire.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.325
But I got this off him
before I blacked out.

10:30.368 --> 10:32.327
You should call your friend
at the DOJ.

10:32.370 --> 10:34.155
We gotta get to a crime lab.

10:34.198 --> 10:37.245
- Yeah, okay, but--
oh, my God.

10:37.288 --> 10:38.768
You need
to get that stitched up.

10:38.812 --> 10:44.687
♪

10:44.731 --> 10:46.689
- Here, you do it.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.648
- What?
[scoffs]

10:48.691 --> 10:50.606
No, I'm not a doctor.

10:50.650 --> 10:53.870
- [laughing]

10:53.914 --> 10:55.872
You can sew, can't you?

10:55.916 --> 10:57.526
- [sighs]

10:57.569 --> 11:02.270
♪

11:02.313 --> 11:04.402
- [groaning]

11:04.446 --> 11:06.535
You almost done?
- Complain this much

11:06.578 --> 11:08.319
when your wife stitched you up?

11:11.540 --> 11:12.672
- No.

11:12.715 --> 11:15.239
[hissing, gasping]

11:15.283 --> 11:16.806
She was innocent.

11:19.156 --> 11:20.723
She's gone.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.856
[brakes hissing]

11:22.899 --> 11:27.251
♪

11:27.295 --> 11:29.253
[drill buzzing]

11:29.297 --> 11:31.647
You and me,
we're as guilty as sin,

11:31.691 --> 11:33.518
but we're still alive.

11:33.562 --> 11:35.172
- For now.

11:36.434 --> 11:43.528
♪

12:06.203 --> 12:07.727
[staple clicks]

12:09.554 --> 12:11.556
[drill hums]

12:14.516 --> 12:21.262
♪

12:38.235 --> 12:40.237
[keypad beeping]

12:42.631 --> 12:44.851
[machine beeping]

12:44.894 --> 12:46.766
- How long is this gonna take?

12:48.593 --> 12:49.856
- I'll call Margo,
see if she can get

12:49.899 --> 12:51.683
more people on it.

12:51.727 --> 12:53.337
Hey, Margo, it's me again.

12:53.381 --> 12:54.686
Call me back.

12:54.730 --> 12:56.776
[phone beeps]

12:58.560 --> 13:02.999
[suspenseful music]

13:03.043 --> 13:08.483
♪

13:08.526 --> 13:10.006
[vending machine clunks]

13:10.050 --> 13:12.313
- Nadine Memphis?
- Yep.

13:14.010 --> 13:15.969
[dramatic sting]

13:18.449 --> 13:21.017
[pop music playing
over speakers]

13:21.061 --> 13:24.020
[tense music]

13:24.064 --> 13:31.288
♪

13:37.947 --> 13:39.427
[dramatic musical sting]

13:39.470 --> 13:46.477
♪

13:58.968 --> 14:00.578
[door rattling]

14:08.630 --> 14:11.633
[dramatic, thrilling music]

14:11.676 --> 14:18.683
♪

14:32.828 --> 14:34.917
- Through that door.

14:34.961 --> 14:42.011
♪

14:46.711 --> 14:48.888
- [panting]

14:48.931 --> 14:50.411
Jesus--
Okay, okay.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.934
Okay, okay, yeah.

14:51.978 --> 14:53.675
Take it--
just take it, it's fine.

14:56.808 --> 14:56.939
.

14:56.983 --> 14:59.855
- The recent death of
Supreme Court Justice nominee

15:01.117 --> 15:01.422
Raymond Brooks,
the final seat

15:02.727 --> 15:03.119
on the Supreme Court
sits vacant.

15:04.816 --> 15:05.034
The President's choice
is expected later this week.

15:06.427 --> 15:06.993
despite many on the Senate
demanding

15:08.342 --> 15:09.038
that the nomination
be postponed.

15:09.082 --> 15:10.692
[knocking on door]

15:14.478 --> 15:17.046
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

15:17.090 --> 15:19.701
- Oh, I missed you.
- Yeah.

15:22.704 --> 15:24.924
- Got us some wine...

15:24.967 --> 15:27.056
room service on the way.

15:33.758 --> 15:35.064
- Bob Lee?

15:38.807 --> 15:40.765
I'm done.

15:40.809 --> 15:43.768
I'm done with you
being an absent father.

15:43.812 --> 15:45.640
I'm done with living in danger.

15:45.683 --> 15:48.599
I'm done with Mary living
in danger.

15:48.643 --> 15:51.080
I'm just done.

15:51.124 --> 15:53.517
[tense music]

15:53.561 --> 15:54.954
- Shit...

15:56.259 --> 15:58.696
When you said you wanted
to meet, I...

16:00.046 --> 16:01.961
never thought
it was about this.

16:03.092 --> 16:04.789
- I know...

16:04.833 --> 16:06.269
but that's the problem.

16:06.313 --> 16:07.923
We're not connected anymore.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.794
You're always away.

16:09.838 --> 16:12.536
And even when you are home,
it's like you're not there.

16:12.580 --> 16:14.756
You're not really with us.
- I don't want to be away

16:14.799 --> 16:16.540
from you and Mary.
I try to keep things separate.

16:16.584 --> 16:18.281
- But even--but even when
I look at you, it's like

16:18.325 --> 16:20.805
there's somewhere else
that you would rather be.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.285
- Hold on, wait a second...
- [stammering]

16:22.329 --> 16:24.287
You're always waiting,
you're always waiting

16:24.331 --> 16:26.028
for something else to happen.

16:26.072 --> 16:28.291
Hoping for it to happen
so you can go off

16:28.335 --> 16:30.163
and--and be a hero again.

16:30.206 --> 16:32.208
[phone vibrating]

16:33.862 --> 16:36.169
- [scoffs]
- I'm not gonna pick up.

16:36.212 --> 16:38.606
- Yes, but that's the problem--
you want to.

16:38.649 --> 16:41.174
- No, I don't.
I'm here with you.

16:41.217 --> 16:42.784
I'm present.

16:46.788 --> 16:48.659
All right now's my turn.

16:50.052 --> 16:52.011
I know this has been hard
on you...

16:53.099 --> 16:54.622
but trying to find out

16:54.665 --> 16:55.927
the truth about my father
was important.

16:55.971 --> 16:57.625
- But it's gone
beyond that, now, Bob Lee.

16:57.668 --> 16:59.627
- That's why
all this shit started.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.281
I couldn't control
where it led me.

17:02.108 --> 17:03.674
Baby, it's not like
you loved it

17:03.718 --> 17:07.852
when I was just home
fixing fences, and...

17:07.896 --> 17:09.637
When Isaac came looking for me,

17:09.680 --> 17:11.073
you were the one who told me
to get back in the fight.

17:11.117 --> 17:12.553
- No, you do not--
- It's true.

17:12.596 --> 17:14.076
- You don't get
to put that on me.

17:14.120 --> 17:15.991
You don't get
to--to play victim?

17:16.035 --> 17:17.166
No one tells you what to do.

17:17.210 --> 17:18.733
If you're in any sort of shit,

17:18.776 --> 17:20.343
it's because you want
to be there.

17:20.387 --> 17:21.953
You know that.

17:26.262 --> 17:28.090
- Yeah.

17:28.134 --> 17:29.570
You're right.

17:31.354 --> 17:32.921
I like the thrill.

17:33.748 --> 17:35.010
Too much.

17:35.967 --> 17:39.232
Serving my country, doing right
by other people,

17:39.275 --> 17:41.060
I get carried away.

17:42.191 --> 17:44.889
[dramatic sting]

17:44.933 --> 17:46.369
- Harris.

17:46.413 --> 17:48.154
Thank you for coming by.
- Uh, yeah.

17:48.197 --> 17:50.678
I wasn't busy, Mr. President.

17:50.721 --> 17:53.724
- So, um, are you
a bourbon man?

17:53.768 --> 17:56.901
- Twenty minutes ago,
I thought I was a dead man.

17:56.945 --> 17:58.077
- Well...

18:01.689 --> 18:03.604
who's to say that's changed?

18:06.172 --> 18:07.825
[laughing]

18:07.869 --> 18:09.914
- [laughs weakly]
- Please, have a seat.

18:13.135 --> 18:15.137
The first day on the job, here,

18:15.181 --> 18:16.747
they tell you five secrets.

18:16.791 --> 18:18.662
I thought it was gonna be
about aliens, and...

18:18.706 --> 18:19.663
[door closes]

18:19.707 --> 18:21.230
Area 51.

18:21.274 --> 18:24.233
The desert island where Elvis
and Marilyn Monroe still live.

18:24.277 --> 18:26.714
Well, no such luck.

18:26.757 --> 18:28.411
It's all about
the terrorists overseas

18:28.455 --> 18:31.240
who want to destroy
our way of life.

18:31.284 --> 18:33.721
And the people here
in this country

18:33.764 --> 18:37.159
who live in the shadows
who have the same objective.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.248
The former groups
are dangerous,

18:39.292 --> 18:41.946
but the latter are even worse.

18:43.905 --> 18:45.907
You know
what I'm talking about.

18:45.950 --> 18:47.126
- Yes, sir.

18:48.301 --> 18:50.172
- I may control the military

18:50.216 --> 18:52.131
and all
the three-letter agencies,

18:52.174 --> 18:54.916
but the truth is, I don't know
who among them I can trust.

18:54.959 --> 18:56.178
- Neither do we.

18:56.222 --> 18:57.962
- What I do know
is an event is imminent

18:58.006 --> 18:59.094
right here in D.C.

19:00.443 --> 19:03.142
I need you to find out
what it is and stop it.

19:05.231 --> 19:07.146
- Why are you asking us?

19:07.189 --> 19:08.712
- Because I knew
the Secret Service

19:08.756 --> 19:10.323
could pick you two up quietly.

19:10.366 --> 19:12.455
But Bob Lee Swagger?

19:12.499 --> 19:14.979
They'd be dead.
[chuckles]

19:19.723 --> 19:22.900
- I never brought danger
to our family.

19:22.944 --> 19:24.685
Someone else
always brought it to me.

19:26.121 --> 19:27.862
- I know.

19:27.905 --> 19:31.213
You're a damn
clusterfu-- magnet.

19:31.257 --> 19:34.912
But still, I mean,
there's--there's a point...

19:34.956 --> 19:37.741
when you could take a step back
and let legitimate authorities

19:37.785 --> 19:39.961
take over, and you never do it.

19:40.004 --> 19:42.137
- Because I can't trust them.

19:42.181 --> 19:44.313
Besides, baby, they can't do
what I do.

19:44.357 --> 19:46.272
- How do you know?
- If there's a chance

19:46.315 --> 19:48.187
that I can save people's lives,
I don't know how to walk away

19:48.230 --> 19:51.233
and just let them die.
- I know that about you.

19:51.277 --> 19:54.149
I'm--I'm not asking...

19:54.193 --> 19:56.804
you to not save lives, I...

19:58.371 --> 20:00.373
We have Mary.

20:00.416 --> 20:02.810
It's reckless and selfish.

20:07.510 --> 20:10.426
- If anything ever happened
to you guys,

20:10.470 --> 20:12.036
I don't know what I'd do.

20:14.256 --> 20:16.476
[hopeful music]

20:16.519 --> 20:17.868
- Hey.

20:17.912 --> 20:19.522
We're okay.

20:19.566 --> 20:22.351
The war in Afghanistan,
it's over for you.

20:22.395 --> 20:25.224
You've had to bury friends
and family,

20:25.267 --> 20:27.748
and you've now solved
your father's murder.

20:29.097 --> 20:30.925
It's time to come home.

20:33.101 --> 20:35.451
Stop trying to save the world.

20:37.888 --> 20:40.108
Save your family instead.

20:43.851 --> 20:45.418
- Okay.

20:45.461 --> 20:50.074
♪

20:50.118 --> 20:51.772
- You expect us to believe

20:51.815 --> 20:53.252
you don't have
three other people

20:53.295 --> 20:55.863
in the whole government
who are capable and loyal?

20:55.906 --> 20:58.257
- You expect me to believe
that my Chief of Staff died

20:58.300 --> 21:00.128
in a drunk driving accident?

21:00.955 --> 21:02.870
I need...

21:02.913 --> 21:05.089
an outsider who still knows

21:05.133 --> 21:07.527
the ins and outs
of law enforcement.

21:07.570 --> 21:11.444
and a belt-weight insider
who knows how to maneuver...

21:11.487 --> 21:12.793
discreetly.

21:14.316 --> 21:17.276
In an ideal world, my gratitude
would be all you'd earn,

21:17.319 --> 21:19.452
but those days
are long gone, so...

21:20.888 --> 21:23.238
Name your price.
- Mm.

21:23.282 --> 21:25.240
Uh, well--
[clears throat]

21:25.284 --> 21:28.417
Speaking of
your Chief of Staff,

21:28.461 --> 21:29.897
have you replaced him?

21:29.940 --> 21:32.073
- [laughing]

21:32.116 --> 21:33.335
What are you, 14?

21:33.379 --> 21:34.597
Get real.

21:34.641 --> 21:37.470
- Uh, how about this, uh...

21:37.513 --> 21:40.124
if I help put a stop to this,

21:40.168 --> 21:42.257
you'll know I'm a man
who can get things done.

21:42.301 --> 21:44.825
You'll also know
you can trust me.

21:44.868 --> 21:45.956
That's more than you ever
could have said

21:46.000 --> 21:47.262
about Andrew Gold.

21:48.916 --> 21:50.309
- I'll think about it.

21:53.355 --> 21:55.966
- If we fail,
we're the bad guys.

21:56.010 --> 21:57.968
That becomes the narrative,
not this.

21:58.012 --> 22:00.319
- Well, that's a chance
you'll have to take.

22:00.362 --> 22:02.451
- Even if we're successful,

22:02.495 --> 22:04.845
you'll still have the problem
of these evil forces

22:04.888 --> 22:08.414
in the shadows here.
- Unless you agree to...

22:08.457 --> 22:11.330
shoulder the burden,
shall we say?

22:11.373 --> 22:13.288
And stop the sky from falling.

22:13.332 --> 22:19.338
♪

22:21.601 --> 22:23.124
- Okay.

22:26.997 --> 22:28.999
You can help us.

22:29.043 --> 22:30.349
Take all Federal government

22:30.392 --> 22:32.133
emergency evacuation plans
offline.

22:32.176 --> 22:33.395
Go old school.

22:33.439 --> 22:34.657
Directions printed up
every day

22:34.701 --> 22:36.529
- That might look suspicious.

22:37.443 --> 22:39.619
- That's a chance
you'll have to take, sir.

22:42.099 --> 22:42.317
.

22:42.361 --> 22:45.494
[phone buzzing]

22:46.321 --> 22:47.061
- Nadine.
- Hey.

22:48.105 --> 22:48.541
You get the results?
- Yeah.

22:49.368 --> 22:50.064
Where the hell did you go?

22:51.152 --> 22:52.066
- [scoffs]
You're not gonna believe it.

22:52.109 --> 22:53.633
Meet us
at Bob Lee's hotel room.

22:59.639 --> 23:01.467
Maybe after
a little family time

23:01.510 --> 23:04.339
at home with Mary...

23:04.383 --> 23:06.297
you and I can go
someplace nice.

23:06.341 --> 23:08.387
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

23:08.430 --> 23:10.432
- Like a real honeymoon?

23:10.476 --> 23:12.391
- [laughs]

23:12.434 --> 23:13.696
- Maybe Hawaii.

23:13.740 --> 23:16.220
- be perfect.
- Yeah.

23:16.264 --> 23:18.701
- A bunch of guys from basic
are serving at Kaneohe Bay,

23:18.745 --> 23:20.573
I haven't seen them
in forever--

23:20.616 --> 23:22.313
[laughing]

23:22.357 --> 23:23.750
- [sighs]
Bob Lee, I'm gonna kill you.

23:23.793 --> 23:25.316
[both laughing]
- I'm sorry, that was mean.

23:25.360 --> 23:26.666
That was mean.

23:30.278 --> 23:31.714
[knocking on door]

23:31.758 --> 23:33.412
- Leave it.
- Okay.

23:34.891 --> 23:36.153
[knocking on door]

23:36.197 --> 23:37.677
- [sighs]

23:37.720 --> 23:38.852
No...
- Just...

23:38.895 --> 23:40.331
[knocking on door]

23:40.375 --> 23:42.725
[mumbles]

23:42.769 --> 23:45.772
[knocking on door continues]

23:47.556 --> 23:48.775
All right!

23:49.776 --> 23:51.430
What?
- We have a lead.

23:51.473 --> 23:53.562
- Good, go chase it.
- It's the Semtex you got

23:53.606 --> 23:56.130
from the Alpha Boys' house.
- We went to Margo.

23:56.173 --> 23:58.306
We tested the trace residue
from the tiki torches--

23:58.349 --> 23:59.655
we got a match.

24:00.656 --> 24:02.745
- To what?
- I got this off the guy

24:02.789 --> 24:03.920
who killed Mayfield.

24:03.964 --> 24:05.879
Remember him?

24:05.922 --> 24:09.143
Probably killed Gregson, too,
and he tried to kill me.

24:13.843 --> 24:15.584
- Know where we just were,
Bob Lee?

24:15.628 --> 24:17.760
The Oval Office.
- What?

24:17.804 --> 24:19.240
- Yeah.
- It's true.

24:19.283 --> 24:21.155
The President wants us
to finish this.

24:22.417 --> 24:24.941
- Last time somebody appealed
to my patriotism,

24:24.985 --> 24:27.204
we all know what happened.
- Well, the President took

24:27.248 --> 24:28.597
the Titan Card out of play.

24:28.641 --> 24:31.208
That's a risk to him.
- Means this time,

24:31.252 --> 24:33.297
you wouldn't be the only one
getting framed.

24:36.518 --> 24:38.607
- "M-C-M-X" is what in--

24:38.651 --> 24:41.654
- Roman numerals for 1910.

24:44.918 --> 24:47.486
Yeah, schools often put
the year that they were founded

24:47.529 --> 24:49.444
on their seal.

24:49.488 --> 24:51.707
[keys tapping]

24:51.751 --> 24:52.795
- "Saint Agatha."

24:52.839 --> 24:55.189
West Oakland, Arlington.
Look.

24:55.232 --> 24:57.321
Pendant matches the logo.

24:57.365 --> 24:58.497
- Let's move.

25:00.673 --> 25:02.718
- Guys, I need a minute, so...

25:02.762 --> 25:06.200
[tense music]

25:06.243 --> 25:13.207
♪

25:13.250 --> 25:14.425
Sweetheart,
this is the last thing

25:14.469 --> 25:16.427
I need to do.

25:16.471 --> 25:18.386
- I'm gonna head home.

25:18.429 --> 25:20.475
Mary needs at least one parent.

25:20.519 --> 25:22.608
- Don't give up on us.

25:22.651 --> 25:24.218
- I'm not mad.

25:25.219 --> 25:26.916
I'm not, honestly.

25:26.960 --> 25:29.571
This is just who you are.

25:29.615 --> 25:32.966
You're the man that runs
towards the bomb and...

25:33.009 --> 25:34.533
not away from one.

25:34.576 --> 25:41.583
♪

25:44.760 --> 25:47.763
[suspenseful music]

25:47.807 --> 25:50.853
♪

25:50.897 --> 25:53.726
[indistinct chatter]

25:53.769 --> 26:00.820
♪

26:05.607 --> 26:07.522
- Is there a problem?

26:07.566 --> 26:10.786
♪

26:10.830 --> 26:12.527
Is the computer running slow?

26:12.571 --> 26:14.573
That's what I'm here to fix.

26:14.616 --> 26:19.795
♪

26:19.839 --> 26:20.883
[metal detector beeps]

26:20.927 --> 26:27.934
♪

26:28.978 --> 26:32.286
[indistinct chatter]

26:53.655 --> 26:54.787
[device beeps]

26:56.092 --> 26:59.443
[computer beeping]

26:59.487 --> 27:06.537
♪

27:14.545 --> 27:15.895
- Come on, kids,
get in to class!

27:15.938 --> 27:17.461
[laughing]

27:17.505 --> 27:20.334
[church bell tolling]

27:20.377 --> 27:22.118
- Morning, sister.

27:22.162 --> 27:23.642
- Good morning.

27:23.685 --> 27:25.469
- Special Agent Johnson,
Secret Service.

27:25.513 --> 27:27.080
Do you have a moment?

27:27.123 --> 27:29.560
- Is something wrong?
- Nothing to be alarmed about.

27:29.604 --> 27:31.040
- We're looking for someone.

27:31.084 --> 27:33.608
We think they may be a member
of your parish.

27:33.652 --> 27:35.044
- Oh, well...

27:35.088 --> 27:36.655
Please come in.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.962
- Yeah, so this guy's
around 5'10",

27:40.006 --> 27:43.705
165 pounds, brown hair,
brown eyes.

27:43.749 --> 27:46.752
- I'm sorry, but we have
over 800 families

27:46.795 --> 27:48.057
and parishioners.

27:48.101 --> 27:50.625
Can you be more specific?

27:50.669 --> 27:52.105
He's a little strange.

27:52.148 --> 27:53.802
Probably keeps to himself.

27:55.456 --> 27:58.459
- Maybe he works here?
- Oh.

27:58.502 --> 28:01.767
Well, I suppose there's
Mr. Martin, our handyman.

28:01.810 --> 28:03.638
Follow me.

28:03.682 --> 28:06.510
I probably wouldn't use
the word "strange,"

28:06.554 --> 28:09.688
but Eli definitely has
his own way about things.

28:11.559 --> 28:14.040
- How long has he worked here?
- He's been with us for years.

28:14.083 --> 28:16.172
He can fix anything.

28:16.216 --> 28:17.652
Comes and goes on his own--

28:17.696 --> 28:19.088
many days
I barely even see him--

28:19.132 --> 28:21.134
but he always pops up
when we need him.

28:21.177 --> 28:24.006
- Is he here now?
- Well, I don't know.

28:24.050 --> 28:25.747
- Do you know
where he might be?

28:25.791 --> 28:28.489
- If I know Eli,
either in the garage,

28:28.532 --> 28:30.534
or the basement.

28:30.578 --> 28:32.536
I hope he's not
in some sort of trouble.

28:32.580 --> 28:34.625
- We just need to talk to him.

28:34.669 --> 28:41.720
♪

28:46.550 --> 28:49.075
So when was the last time
you saw him?

28:49.118 --> 28:51.425
- Um, let's see...

28:53.557 --> 28:55.472
Oh, yesterday!

28:55.516 --> 28:58.780
He told me he had to take one
of our buses to the mechanics.

28:58.824 --> 29:05.526
♪

29:06.875 --> 29:08.790
Oh, look, he must be in.

29:08.834 --> 29:11.967
He always turns his light off
when he leaves.

29:12.011 --> 29:15.014
[dramatic music]

29:15.057 --> 29:22.108
♪

29:35.469 --> 29:37.645
- Hold up, hold up--wait!
- He's getting away!

29:37.688 --> 29:39.125
- I think he rigged
the door, man.

29:41.170 --> 29:42.998
Shit.

29:45.479 --> 29:46.915
Take cover.

29:46.959 --> 29:54.009
♪

29:57.970 --> 29:58.187
.

29:58.231 --> 30:00.624
[suspenseful music]

30:01.538 --> 30:02.322
- You good?
- Yeah, you?

30:02.365 --> 30:04.846
- Yeah.
- Careful.

30:04.890 --> 30:09.677
♪

30:09.720 --> 30:11.070
- He's long gone.

30:11.113 --> 30:18.120
♪

30:21.341 --> 30:23.125
- Comes back to change?

30:24.910 --> 30:27.086
She said he could fix anything,
then she said

30:27.129 --> 30:29.001
he takes the bus
to the mechanic.

30:29.044 --> 30:31.438
Don't you think that's weird?

30:31.481 --> 30:34.267
[approaching sirens]

30:34.310 --> 30:41.317
♪

30:45.800 --> 30:46.975
Got you.

30:52.154 --> 30:54.200
Got a open door left.
- All right.

30:54.243 --> 30:59.901
♪

30:59.945 --> 31:01.337
Short room.

31:02.730 --> 31:03.731
Clear.

31:03.774 --> 31:10.825
♪

31:19.355 --> 31:21.444
He's been building a bomb
in here.

31:21.488 --> 31:23.142
- And didn't clean up.

31:23.185 --> 31:24.970
- Man, you saw the basement.

31:25.013 --> 31:27.146
This guy's prepared,
he's meticulous.

31:27.189 --> 31:29.888
But he runs back here
to get changed

31:29.931 --> 31:31.498
after his run in with you?

31:31.541 --> 31:33.761
Doesn't make sense.
It's like he's scrambling.

31:33.804 --> 31:35.894
Bus is gone...
- Shit.

31:35.937 --> 31:37.373
The attack is today.

31:37.417 --> 31:39.462
- What's the target?

31:39.506 --> 31:41.464
- Okay, come on!
Let's do it!

31:41.508 --> 31:43.118
Single file,
quick, quick, quick!

31:43.162 --> 31:44.728
Very exciting, big day.

31:44.772 --> 31:45.991
Watch your step,
one at a time,

31:46.034 --> 31:47.296
One at a time.

31:47.340 --> 31:49.951
[children giggling, chattering]

31:49.995 --> 31:53.476
- Very exciting day.
No pushing. But quickly.

31:53.520 --> 31:56.958
[sinister music]

31:57.002 --> 31:58.525
Okay.

31:58.568 --> 32:01.354
So who's excited to go visit
the Supreme Court today?

32:01.397 --> 32:03.791
[all cheering]

32:03.834 --> 32:05.445
Very good!

32:05.488 --> 32:07.795
And away we go!

32:07.838 --> 32:13.061
♪

32:15.890 --> 32:17.239
- Eli Aaron Martin.

32:17.283 --> 32:18.980
Born Kansas City, Missouri,

32:19.024 --> 32:21.374
18th of May, 1978.

32:21.417 --> 32:25.465
Died 21st of May, 1978,

32:25.508 --> 32:27.510
Kansas City, Kansas.

32:27.554 --> 32:29.034
- I don't get it.

32:29.077 --> 32:30.470
- You apply
for a birth certificate

32:30.513 --> 32:31.950
for someone who was born
around your birthday,

32:31.993 --> 32:33.386
but died as an infant.

32:33.429 --> 32:35.910
State records, Social Security
rarely cross-check,

32:35.954 --> 32:37.564
especially across state lines.

32:37.607 --> 32:39.783
You get yourself
a whole new identity.

32:40.871 --> 32:42.221
- Martin's not Martin.

32:42.264 --> 32:44.440
It's a dead end.
- Figures.

32:44.484 --> 32:46.007
How do we find him?

32:47.052 --> 32:48.967
- Well, he's Atlas' fixer,
right?

32:49.010 --> 32:51.404
- Yeah.
- So what did he have to fix?

32:53.101 --> 32:56.017
[suspenseful music]

32:56.061 --> 32:58.237
- It's always been about Brooks
and the Supreme Court.

32:58.280 --> 32:59.934
- What's the final check

32:59.978 --> 33:02.067
on absolute power
in government?

33:02.110 --> 33:04.025
- The Supreme Court.
- Control that,

33:04.069 --> 33:05.592
control everything.

33:05.635 --> 33:08.551
- Atlas knew there'd be
opposition to Brooks...

33:08.595 --> 33:11.119
and Hayes was
their political muscle, right?

33:11.163 --> 33:13.208
- Uh, there was nobody better
at whipping Senators

33:13.252 --> 33:15.950
into line, yeah.
- Yeah, then Hayes dies.

33:15.994 --> 33:17.082
- You're having
a heart attack, Senator.

33:17.125 --> 33:19.519
- [gasping]

33:19.562 --> 33:21.564
- Atlas needs a new way
to switch those votes.

33:21.608 --> 33:23.044
- And instead
of swinging them...

33:23.088 --> 33:24.306
- They went all in.

33:24.350 --> 33:26.004
- Brooks dies...

33:27.309 --> 33:28.571
- But Atlas is still coming.

33:28.615 --> 33:30.530
- Because the problem
doesn't go away.

33:30.573 --> 33:33.315
Anhur Dynamics is a case
that could expose Atlas.

33:33.359 --> 33:34.838
All their secrets.

33:34.882 --> 33:36.362
There's a 4-4 split
on the court.

33:36.405 --> 33:38.016
- Brooks would have
made it 5-4.

33:38.059 --> 33:40.844
- Also just found out
there is no backup nominee.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.500
- So Atlas can't sub in
for Brooks...

33:46.111 --> 33:48.504
but 4-3 would still win it
for him.

33:48.548 --> 33:50.376
- Holy shit.

33:50.419 --> 33:52.856
- They're gonna kill
a Supreme Court Justice.

33:53.596 --> 33:55.207
[sirens whooping]

33:55.250 --> 33:57.992
[indistinct radio chatter]

33:58.036 --> 34:00.995
[sinister music]

34:01.039 --> 34:07.958
♪

34:10.091 --> 34:12.224
[indistinct chatter]

34:12.267 --> 34:19.318
♪

34:31.895 --> 34:35.160
[radio chatter]

34:35.203 --> 34:42.167
♪

34:42.210 --> 34:44.169
[kids chattering]

34:44.212 --> 34:50.044
♪

34:50.088 --> 34:53.395
- [groaning]
- Hey, man, you okay?

34:53.439 --> 35:00.489
♪

35:02.709 --> 35:04.537
- Okay, now,
this dog is working.

35:04.580 --> 35:07.061
He's not a pet,
so no petting.

35:07.105 --> 35:10.020
Everybody get your knees
and your hands inside.

35:10.064 --> 35:12.719
We're just gonna let him
do his job.

35:12.762 --> 35:15.156
No moving, no petting.

35:15.200 --> 35:16.505
[radio chatter]

35:16.549 --> 35:18.246
- We wouldn't pet a cop
on his head,

35:18.290 --> 35:21.467
so we don't pet a working dog
on his head.

35:21.510 --> 35:24.557
He's a police officer,
but he's just a dog.

35:24.600 --> 35:26.298
And what do we say?

35:26.341 --> 35:28.256
all: Thank you.

35:28.300 --> 35:35.350
♪

35:47.406 --> 35:47.623
.

35:47.667 --> 35:49.886
- I don't see
a St. Agatha bus.

35:51.192 --> 35:51.410
- He wouldn't have shown up
in the morning

35:52.585 --> 35:53.368
on an empty bus.
- We have his face now.

35:54.500 --> 35:55.718
No way he'd have risked
driving, either.

36:00.201 --> 36:01.855
- Okay.

36:01.898 --> 36:04.031
That nun said he took the bus
to a mechanic--

36:04.074 --> 36:05.511
maybe he had it repainted

36:05.554 --> 36:07.034
to match
a Maryland Unified bus.

36:07.077 --> 36:08.862
We gotta go bus to bus,
scratch off some paint--

36:08.905 --> 36:11.038
see if we can find
the St. Agatha logo underneath.

36:11.081 --> 36:13.171
[children chattering]

36:13.214 --> 36:20.395
♪

36:34.801 --> 36:37.891
[police radio chatter]

36:40.633 --> 36:42.809
- Guys, I got it!
- Yeah.

36:42.852 --> 36:48.728
♪

36:48.771 --> 36:50.643
- What's going on, here?

36:50.686 --> 36:51.992
- FBI.

36:53.950 --> 36:55.735
- See some ID?

36:55.778 --> 36:59.173
- Uh, we got...
- [indistinct]

36:59.217 --> 37:01.001
- Nadine, what's the code
for a bomb?

37:01.044 --> 37:03.525
- Uh, 98.
- Uh, this is Officer Murphy.

37:03.569 --> 37:05.179
I got a Code 98
at the Supreme Court!

37:05.223 --> 37:06.789
I repeat, a Code 98!

37:06.833 --> 37:08.226
Evacuate the area immediately!

37:08.269 --> 37:10.619
- Harris, get everyone out
of here, now.

37:10.663 --> 37:17.713
♪

37:29.986 --> 37:32.989
[sinister music]

37:33.033 --> 37:40.083
♪

37:42.042 --> 37:44.000
- Shit.

37:44.044 --> 37:46.133
Found the remote detonator.

37:46.176 --> 37:48.527
- It's gotta be connected
wirelessly to the master.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.268
- All right,
look for fresh staples

37:50.311 --> 37:52.139
under the seats.
- Please, get out of here.

37:52.182 --> 37:54.228
It's not safe here.
[stammering]

37:54.272 --> 37:55.795
Keep moving--
please keep moving.

37:55.838 --> 38:00.060
♪

38:00.103 --> 38:02.715
- I found the master detonator.

38:02.758 --> 38:04.282
- What the hell
are you gonna do?

38:04.325 --> 38:05.848
- Diffuse it.

38:05.892 --> 38:07.328
There could be over 20 pounds
of Semtex in here.

38:07.372 --> 38:09.287
- Probably Semtex
all over the place.

38:09.330 --> 38:11.898
- The explosion is a diversion
to get the Justices evacuating.

38:11.941 --> 38:13.769
- Yeah, but the Titan card
doesn't work,

38:13.813 --> 38:16.076
so maybe he's going
to Oklahoma City.

38:16.119 --> 38:18.165
- I'll evacuate the area.

38:18.208 --> 38:20.036
Hey, are you okay?

38:20.080 --> 38:21.647
Come on, I need your help.

38:21.690 --> 38:23.518
Let's go.
- Please, uh, keep--

38:23.562 --> 38:24.954
keep moving,
please keep moving.

38:24.998 --> 38:26.565
It's--it's not--
- FBI!

38:26.608 --> 38:28.044
Evacuate the area!

38:28.088 --> 38:30.003
- Move out of the--
- Evacuate the area, now!

38:30.046 --> 38:31.309
[people screaming]

38:31.352 --> 38:34.094
- FBI!
Evacuate the area!

38:34.137 --> 38:36.575
[suspenseful music]

38:36.618 --> 38:38.098
- All right.

38:38.141 --> 38:40.187
Explosives, power...

38:40.230 --> 38:42.058
timer, detonator.

38:42.102 --> 38:44.104
Just like you told me
in those IED briefings.

38:44.147 --> 38:45.366
- This thing
is way more complicated

38:45.410 --> 38:48.021
than any IED we ever found.

38:48.064 --> 38:49.675
What are you doing?

38:49.718 --> 38:52.547
- Gonna stop it
from powering up.

38:52.591 --> 38:53.983
Red or black?

38:55.898 --> 38:57.291
- Fu-- it.

38:57.335 --> 39:01.817
♪

39:01.861 --> 39:03.819
[phone whines]

39:03.863 --> 39:05.560
- Oh, shit.

39:05.604 --> 39:07.301
- It's too late,
we can't stop it.

39:07.345 --> 39:08.868
We gotta move.

39:08.911 --> 39:10.652
- Oh, shit.

39:10.696 --> 39:12.828
Let's go!
Go, go, go, go!

39:15.309 --> 39:17.050
- FBI!
Evacuate, evacuate!

39:17.093 --> 39:18.399
- Everybody down!

39:18.443 --> 39:19.879
- Mom?

39:19.922 --> 39:21.359
Mom!

39:21.402 --> 39:23.709
Mom--
[gasps]

39:23.752 --> 39:25.928
[phone beeps]

39:33.849 --> 39:36.678
[high-pitched ringing]

39:36.722 --> 39:39.681
[tense music]

39:39.725 --> 39:46.340
♪

39:46.384 --> 39:47.907
[screaming fades in]

39:47.950 --> 39:49.169
- Get out of here,
get out of here.

39:49.212 --> 39:50.953
Go, go, go!

39:50.997 --> 39:53.086
- Mommy!

39:53.129 --> 39:55.915
[people screaming]

39:55.958 --> 39:57.743
- Where you going?
- Supreme Court!

39:57.786 --> 39:59.266
Titan card doesn't work,
he's gotta pick up

39:59.309 --> 40:00.833
his target there!

40:02.051 --> 40:03.618
- [panting]

40:03.662 --> 40:05.315
[groans]

40:06.273 --> 40:08.014
- Nadine!

40:08.057 --> 40:10.103
- [gasping]

40:10.146 --> 40:12.018
- You okay?
- Yeah..

40:13.106 --> 40:15.064
Just go help Bob Lee.

40:15.108 --> 40:16.326
- Nope, it's my turn
to stitch you up.

40:16.370 --> 40:19.068
- [groaning]

40:19.112 --> 40:24.944
♪

40:24.987 --> 40:26.989
[indistinct chatter]

40:28.774 --> 40:30.297
- Shelter in place, sir.

40:30.340 --> 40:33.082
- Uh, no, I get evacuated
with POTUS.

40:33.126 --> 40:35.694
♪

40:35.737 --> 40:37.652
- He took you off
that list, sir.

40:42.004 --> 40:43.789
- Everybody, let's go!

40:43.832 --> 40:45.965
Go, go!

40:46.008 --> 40:48.271
- Thank you, calmly, quietly...

40:48.315 --> 40:52.058
♪

40:52.101 --> 40:55.496
Thank you. Thank you--
calmly, quietly.

40:55.540 --> 40:56.932
Thank you.

40:56.976 --> 40:58.368
Ladies and gentlemen,
calmly...

40:58.412 --> 40:59.500
[approaching sirens]

40:59.544 --> 41:01.763
Quietly, thank you.

41:01.807 --> 41:08.335
♪

41:08.378 --> 41:11.207
[sirens wailing]

41:11.251 --> 41:13.732
- Justice, uh, you've been
ordered to evacuate.

41:13.775 --> 41:15.124
- Well, I'm busy.

41:15.168 --> 41:17.518
[sirens wailing]

41:17.562 --> 41:18.824
Do not.

41:18.867 --> 41:22.784
♪

41:22.828 --> 41:24.046
Seems contained.

41:24.090 --> 41:26.179
Why don't you just
guard me here?

41:27.485 --> 41:29.748
- Justice, you either
walk out of here,

41:29.791 --> 41:32.359
or we will drag you
kicking and screaming.

41:32.402 --> 41:35.014
- Nobody wants to see that.

41:35.057 --> 41:40.106
♪

41:40.149 --> 41:41.499
- Let's go.

41:45.415 --> 41:45.546
.

41:45.807 --> 41:48.418
[suspenseful music]

41:48.984 --> 41:55.513
♪
